rms originate from the time-reversal breaking\nfluctuation of the Chern-Simons gauge fields. We present a perturbative\ncomputation of the Hall viscosity and also show that this term is also obtained\nby a Ward identity. We show that the disclination of the nematic fluid, carries\nan electric charge. We show that a resonance observed in radio-frequency\nconductivity experiments can be interpreted as a Goldstone nematic mode gapped\nby lattice effects.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Feb 2016 21:16:45 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 17 Apr 2016 23:03:48 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 3 May 2016 03:14:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-04"}
